narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The most amazing class you will ever take at Yale.
Definitely take this class. Sumarsam seems happy all the time, which makes for a great environment for learning Gamelan. Anyone could learn these instruments. Highly recommend!!
A phenomenal way to open your eyes to another culture's musical traditions and techniques.
Great way to get hands on with a new instrument, especially if you're interested in ethnomusicology. A bit unstructured.

I would absolutely recommend this course if you are interested in world music. I have taken many music classes here at Yale but none covered Javanese music; it was so interesting to be exposed to a different form of tonality and to learn to play new instruments as an ensemble. Sumarsam is also incredibly knowledgeable. Great experience.
